<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About Us - CineReviews</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/stylesheets/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/leaflet/dist/leaflet.css" />
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/leaflet/dist/leaflet.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
{{{header}}}

<main class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="text-center mb-4">About Us</h1>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <p class="lead text-justify">
            <strong>CineReviews</strong> is the go-to destination for all cinema enthusiasts who want to stay updated
            on the latest news, dive deep into the details of the most anticipated films, and discover the faces
            behind the scenes of the film industry.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Our Passion for Cinema</h2>
        <p class="text-justify">
            Born from the passion of a group of dedicated movie lovers, <strong>CineReviews</strong> is committed to
            providing in-depth reviews, exclusive previews, and detailed articles about films, actors, directors,
            and cinematic events. From indie productions to major blockbusters, our goal is to explore the world
            of cinema in all its forms, celebrating its diversity and creativity.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="text-justify">
            Our mission is simple: to deliver high-quality content that informs, inspires, and engages our readers,
            taking them on a journey through the vast cinematic landscape. Whether it’s reviewing the latest box
            office hit, interviewing emerging talents, or delving into the themes and techniques behind timeless
            masterpieces, we strive to create a rich and comprehensive experience.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Meet Our Team</h2>
        <p class="text-justify">
            The editorial team at <strong>CineReviews</strong> consists of three passionate experts:
            <strong>Lorenzo Sacchetti</strong>, <strong>Federico Santorsola</strong>, and
            <strong>Davide Vercelli</strong>. United by their love for cinema and a desire to share the magic of the
            big screen with their readers, they work tirelessly to bring the best of the cinematic world to you.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Stay Updated</h2>
        <p class="text-justify">
            Every day, we enrich our site with fresh content, including reviews, in-depth articles, news, and
            interviews, to offer a complete overview of the cinematic world. <strong>CineReviews</strong> is the
            perfect place for anyone who wants to immerse themselves in the fascinating universe of cinema and stay
            up-to-date on the latest trends.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Where to Find Us</h2>
        <div id="map" style="width: 100%; height: 400px; border: 1px solid #ccc; border-radius: 8px;"></div>
        <script>
            // Initialize the map
            const map = L.map('map').setView([45.0703, 7.6869], 16);

            // Add OpenStreetMap tiles
            L.tileLayer('https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png', {
                maxZoom: 19,
                attribution: '© OpenStreetMap contributors'
            }).addTo(map);

            // Add a marker for the Dipartimento di Informatica
            L.marker([45.0703, 7.6869]).addTo(map)
                    .bindPopup("<b>Dipartimento di Informatica</b><br>Università degli Studi di Torino")
                    .openPopup();
        </script>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-5">
        <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Contact Information</h2>
        <address>
            <strong>CineReviews Srl</strong><br>
            P. IVA 1234567890<br>
            Ingresso da, C.so Svizzera 185, Via Pessinetto, 12<br>
            10149 Torino TO<br>
            Tel. 011 670 6711<br>
        </address>
    </section>
</main>

{{{footer}}}
</body>
</html>
